ergy as expected from the approximately constant total\nbaryon density above 20 GeV, and the latter show agreement with the CERES\nmeasurement at SPS energy. The consistency in excess yields and agreement with\nmodel calculations over the wide RHIC energy regime makes a strong case for LMR\nenhancements on the order of a factor 2-3.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Apr 2017 21:08:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-24"}
