$\npc$^{-2}$. The CO-to-H$_2$ ratio steadily increases within the first 2 Myr\nwhereas $X_\\mathrm{CO}\\simeq$ 1 - 4 $\\times$ 10$^{20}$ cm$^{-2}$ (K km\ns$^{-1}$)$^{-1}$ is approximately constant since the CO(1-0) line quickly\nbecomes optically thick.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Apr 2017 11:34:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Jul 2017 13:12:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 6 Sep 2017 15:29:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-18"}
